content: Hello! How can I assist you with your nutrition or meal planning today?
which aliment  has more protein , im vegeterian. give 2 options

As a vegetarian, some good protein-rich options include:

1. **Lentils:** Lentils are a rich source of protein and fiber. They can be added to salads, soups, stews, or made into veggie burgers for a satisfying meal.

2. **Quinoa:** Quinoa is a complete protein source, meaning it contains all nine essential amino acids. It can be used as a base for salads, stir-fries, or as a side dish.

These options can help you meet your protein needs as a vegetarian.
You're welcome! If you have any more questions or need further assistance with your nutrition, feel free to ask. Have a great day!
